headline: US Blue-Chip Bond Issuance Reaches Second-Highest Level Ever
summary: (Bloomberg) -- High-grade corporate bond sales in the US this year have climbed to the second-highest level on record as companies rush to take advantage of relatively affordable borrowing costs before the year ends. headline: General Mills Quarterly Dividend Declared
summary: MINNEAPOLIS, November 18, 2024--The General Mills Board of Directors has declared a quarterly dividend at the prevailing rate of $0.60 per share, payable February 3, 2025, to shareholders of record as of January 10, 2025. General Mills (NYSE: GIS) and its predecessor company have paid dividends without interruption for 126 years.
